== 分析 ==
=== 时间循环 ===
众多评论探讨菲尔究竟困在时间循环多长时间<ref name="Hollywoodreporterhanks" /><ref name="IFC">{{cite web | first = Matt | last = Singer | url = https://www.ifc.com/2011/02/the-precise-number-of-groundho | title = The Precise Number of Groundhog Days in "Groundhog Day" | date = 2011-02-07 | publisher = IFC | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200921074109/https://www.ifc.com/2011/02/the-precise-number-of-groundho | dead-url = yes | archive-date = 2020-09-21 | access-date = 2020-09-21 }}</ref>，雷米斯一度表示电影时间距度超过十年<ref name="Hollywoodreporterhanks" />。博客发文估计实际跨度约为九年，雷米斯表示不管九年还是之前自认的十年都不靠谱，理由是冰雕、法语等特长每项都需要至少十年养成，“再考虑休息、走弯路浪费的时间，他至少需要30乃至40年”<ref>{{cite journal | title = Harold Ramis's Response to the Groundhog Day Timeline Study | url = http://heebmagazine.com/harold-ramiss-response-to-the-_groundhog-day_-timeline-study/4575 | journal = Heeb | date = 2009-08-18 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | dead-url = no | archive-date = 2016-03-30 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160330150925/http://heebmagazine.com/harold-ramiss-response-to-the-_groundhog-day_-timeline-study/4575 }}</ref>。另有评论表达类似看法，估计至少需要一万小时才可能精通某领域，根据片中已知情节和循环次数，同时考虑菲尔每天钻研的时间，他很可能被困约1.24万天，近34年<ref name="IFC" />。从鲁宾的剧本原稿来看，菲尔自认困在时间循环70到80年，利用书籍判断过去的时间<ref name="DOGRubin" />。

雷米斯生于犹太家族，但再婚后改习[[佛教|佛教]]生活方式，接受部分佛教戒律<ref name="new yorker" /><ref name="LionsRoad">{{cite journal | last = Garfinkel | first = Perry | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112041809/https://www.lionsroar.com/harold-ramis-profile-by-perry-garfinkel/ | url = https://www.lionsroar.com/harold-ramis-profile-by-perry-garfinkel/ | title = Harold Ramis didn’t intend “Groundhog Day” to be Buddhist, but it’s a dharma classic | journal = Lion's Roar | date = 2018-02-02 | archive-date = 2020-11-12 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="NationalReview">{{Cite journal | first = Jonah | last = Goldberg | dead-url = no | url = https://www.nationalreview.com/2017/02/a-movie-for-all-time/ | title = A Movie for All Time | date = 2017-02-02 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | journal = [[國家評論|National Review]] | archive-date = 2020-11-11 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201111182621/https://www.nationalreview.com/2017/02/a-movie-for-all-time/ }}</ref>。据他透露，根据佛教教义，灵魂需要约一万年才能进化到下一阶段<ref name="Varietyat25" />。鲁宾于2005年表示：“循环持续时长已变成奇怪的政治问题，如果直接去问制片商‘循环持续多久？’他们就回答‘两周’。在我看来，电影想要表达的是你必须感觉已经忍受某种情况很长时间……我也说不大準，但至少也有一百年，一辈子吧。”<ref name="Gilbey-2004" />{{rp|19}}瑞安·吉尔比（{{lang|en|Ryan Gilbey}}）的电影同名著作认为，本片的一大成就便是循环持续时间模糊不定，与片中不解释菲尔如何被困、又为何身陷其中一样，循环持续时间就是菲尔到底需要多久才能改头换面，重新做人<ref name="TheGuardianDirectors" />。

=== 主题分析 ===
[[File:Plaosan_Bodhisattva_02.jpg|thumb]]浮雕。评论认为菲尔·康纳斯就像菩萨，帮忙他人达成[[涅槃|涅槃]]]]

影评人从不同角度解读本片<ref name="VultureRubin" /><ref name="new yorker" />。鲁宾自称无意将本片写成灵魂寓言，只想讲述人生经历，以及身陷循环无从逃脱的处境<ref>{{cite web | first = Phil | last = Hornshaw | title = Listen to Ned Ryerson Tell Behind-the-Scenes Stories About 'Groundhog Day' | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201125115430/https://www.thewrap.com/ned-ryerson-behind-the-scenes-groundhog-day/ | url = https://www.thewrap.com/ned-ryerson-behind-the-scenes-groundhog-day/ | date = 2018-02-02 | website = TheWrap | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-date = 2020-11-25 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。在他看来，本片讲述的“（不）只是人重复某一天，而是应该如何生活。谁的生活不是由很多天组成？又有谁不会时常感到身陷困境？”<ref name="telegraph interview" />菲尔在保龄球馆询问庞克瑟托尼居民，是否理解陷入困境、无论如何都无法摆脱是什么感受。他说的是自身经历，两位居民没有身陷循环，但完全理解他所说的处境。<ref name="NYTReview" />

鲁宾和雷米斯从哲学和精神角度探讨本片，但两人的设想“只是讲述美好、贴心而有趣的故事”<ref name="telegraph interview" />。默瑞认为剧本核心是人们害怕变革而不断重复人生经历<ref name="PhillyBeast" />，鲁宾进一步指出，循环开始当天正是菲尔最倒霉的一天。时间循环强迫他改头换面，拥抱身边的世界和这天的每分每秒，最后这便是他最美好的一天，坠入爱河的一天。<ref name="bigthink rubin" />默瑞在2017年接受采访时称，《土拨鼠之日》的“构想如此美好有力……值得我们一再回味”，相信电影仍能激起共鸣<ref>{{cite journal | first = Daniel | last = Kreps | title = Bill Murray Moved to Tears Over 'Groundhog Day' Broadway Musical | url = https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/bill-murray-moved-to-tears-over-groundhog-day-broadway-musical-122784/ | date = 2017-08-09 | journal = [[滾石_(雜誌)|Rolling Stone]] | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200928164410/https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/bill-murray-moved-to-tears-over-groundhog-day-broadway-musical-122784/ | archive-date = 2020-09-28 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

专业人士多年来相继联络鲁宾提出见解<ref name="IndependentThemes">{{cite news | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101024191105/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/the-greatest-story-ever-told-568494.html | title = The greatest story ever told? | date = 2004-02-02 | dead-url = yes | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/the-greatest-story-ever-told-568494.html | newspaper = The Independent | access-date = 2010-10-24 | archive-date = 2010-10-24 }}</ref>。有人把本片视为基督教寓言，土拨鼠菲尔代表[[耶稣|耶稣]]<ref name="IndependentThemes" />；或把时间循环视为[[弗里德里希·尼采的哲學思想|尼采]][[永恒轮回|永恒轮回]]哲学、犹太教精神，以及[[顺势疗法|顺势疗法]]的本质<ref name="bigthink rubin" /><ref name="VultureRubin" />。还有评论认为电影是希腊神话人物[[西西弗斯|西西弗斯]]的经历改编，西西弗斯同样身陷每天持续不断，直至永恒的惩罚<ref name="ConsequenceofSound">{{cite journal | first = Andrew | last = Bloom | title = Groundhog Day at 25: Bill Murray Finds Freedom While Trapped in a Nightmare | url = https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/02/groundhog-day-at-25-bill-murray-finds-freedom-while-trapped-in-a-nightmare/ | date = 2018-02-18 | journal = [[前音後果|Consequence of Sound]] | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200823171503/https://consequenceofsound.net/2018/02/groundhog-day-at-25-bill-murray-finds-freedom-while-trapped-in-a-nightmare/ | archive-date = 2020-08-23 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。部分文章声称片中数字也有重要意义<ref name="VultureRubin" />，雷米斯对鲁宾的剧本初稿及其转世构想深感着迷<ref name="TheWrapRubin">{{cite web | first = Brian | last = Welk | title = 'Groundhog Day': How Bill Murray Rom-Com Became an Accidental Classic | url = https://www.thewrap.com/groundhog-day-bill-murray-accidental-classic/ | date = 2020-02-01 | website = TheWrap | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201109042306/https://www.thewrap.com/groundhog-day-bill-murray-accidental-classic/ | archive-date = 2020-11-09 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。作家分析片中日期，认为冬天结束代表讽刺等负面情节告终，春天代表喜剧，代表改头换面、重新做人的主题，《土拨鼠之日》就像节日本身的预测那样代表冬季结束、春天开始<ref name="Glausser-2019">{{cite journal | last = Glausser | first = Wayne | title = Groundhog Day at 25: Conflict and Inspiration at the Tipping Point of Seasonal Genres | url = https://digitalcommons.unomaha.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1994&context=jrf | year = 2019 | access-date = 2021-01-17 | publisher = University of Nebraska Omaha | volume = 23 | issue = 1 | journal = Journal of Religion and Film | location = [[奥马哈_(内布拉斯加州)|Omaha, Nebraska]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200705142135/https://digitalcommons.unomaha.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1994&context=jrf | archive-date = 2020-07-05 | dead-url = no }}</ref>{{rp|3, 7}}。

佛教领袖认可片中呈现的转生意识形态。菲尔就像[[菩萨|菩萨]]，达到[[涅槃|涅槃]]边缘后返回人间，帮助他人前往。犹太教将默瑞摆脱时间循环视为他返回人间行使天神戒律和诫命的奖励。基督教把菲尔的旅程视为复生，或是取得天堂一席之地的手段。[[法轮功|法轮功]]宗教哲学认为影片表达的理念，是灵魂必须吸取过去失误的教训才能进化。<ref name="IndependentThemes" /><ref name="TheWrapRubin" /><ref>{{cite news | first = Alex | last = Kuczynski | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2003/12/07/style/groundhog-almighty.html | title = Groundhog Almighty | newspaper = The New York Times | date = 2003-12-07 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201217194256/https://www.nytimes.com/2003/12/07/style/groundhog-almighty.html | archive-date = 2020-12-17 | dead-url = no }}</ref>天主教将菲尔所处困境视为[[炼狱|炼狱]]，只有无私才能解脱<ref name="NationalReview" />。麦克道威尔表示：“如果大家都能有如此经历并从中学到东西该多好，我们有时根本没有意识到生命流逝……无论信仰什么，最后都会成为我们的人生意义所在”<ref name="TheWrapRubin" />。《土拨鼠之日》还可以理解成世俗童话，菲尔身陷生存危机，已经无法满足原始的放纵，导致他身心俱疲，靠改善自我摆脱困难，进而改头换面帮助他人<ref name="Glausser-2019" />{{rp|16}}。

菲尔起初自比天神，身为天气预报员宣称天气就是他说了算<ref name="TheWrapRubin" />。经过多次循环他开始自以为是神，断言神无所不能不过是活得太久，所以什么都懂<ref name="NationalReview" />。他利用知识按意愿操纵形势<ref name="LionsRoad" />，循环还令他得以摆脱自恋带来的自我禁锢。他不愿改变自我，但却不得不这么做。<ref name="LionsRoad" />面对理想爱侣丽塔的一再拒绝，菲尔的情绪降至最低点并反复自杀。甚至觉得自杀这么多次，应该足以让他变得完全不存在。雷米斯指出，菲尔正是此时开始准备改变。<ref name="LionsRoad" /><ref name="ConsequenceofSound" />

菲尔不再利用循环放纵自身欲望，转为无私帮助他人后才摆脱循环<ref name="LATIMesRamis" />。他一再努力挽救无家可归老人的生命，但都以失败告终，被迫接受他不是神的现实<ref>{{cite web | first = Rob | last = Hunter | title = 27 Things We Learned From Harold Ramis' 'Groundhog Day' Commentary | url = https://filmschoolrejects.com/27-things-we-learned-from-harold-ramis-groundhog-day-commentary-c229406e5d46/ | date = 2014-02-27 | website = Film School Rejects | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-date = 2020-11-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201123035848/https://filmschoolrejects.com/27-things-we-learned-from-harold-ramis-groundhog-day-commentary-c229406e5d46/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。与此同时，无论他对丽塔有多么了解，或是通过循环学会多少特长都无法打动并赢得她的爱。只有在他不再以此为目的，真心无私地关怀、帮助他人，明知这一天很可能又会重新开始，所做的一切都没有意义时，才获得丽塔的情感认同。<ref name="new yorker" /><ref name="LATIMesRamis" /><ref name="ConsequenceofSound" />菲尔在片头嘲笑丽塔的为人处事，但这些特点最后都成为他钦佩和尊重的品质，菲尔一心想要时无法赢得丽塔的爱，而是逐渐变成丽塔会爱的人<ref>{{cite book | last = Racicot | first = William | editor-last = Marshall | editor-first = David W. | title = Mass Market Medieval: Essays on the Middle Ages in Popular Culture | chapter = Anything Different is Good: Incremental Repetition, Courtly Love, and Purgatory in ''Groundhog Day'' | year = 2006 | publisher = [[麥克法蘭公司出版社|McFarland Publishing]] | location = Jefferson, North Carolina | access-date = 2021-01-17 | isbn = 978-0-78642-922-6 | pages = 194–195 | url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=LroNNbbvcBoC&redir_esc=y}}</ref>。雷米斯希望借此强调爱令人彻底改变的巨大力量<ref name="PhillyBeast" /><ref name="ConsequenceofSound" />，在他看来，《土拨鼠之日》代表面临重复过去失误的局面时，拥有改变的力量和知识<ref name="LionsRoad" />。

里克·布鲁克海瑟（{{lang|en|Rick Brookhiser}}）指出，菲尔全面认识并接受这一天后才摆脱循环，在他看来，“爱生活就要爱它的每一步”<ref name="NationalReview" />。约翰·西蒙（{{lang|en|John Seamon}}）认为，其他电影用回忆来思考或逃避，菲尔就在永无止境的回忆中生活，一切都会不断重复，根本没有未来。菲尔靠记忆并欣赏新细节来成长，逐渐引导自我转变。<ref>{{cite book | last = Seamon | first = John | title = Memory and Movies: What Films Can Teach Us about Memory | publisher = [[麻省理工学院出版社|MIT Press]] | location = [[剑桥_(马萨诸塞州)|Cambridge, Massachusetts]] | year = 2015 | access-date = 2021-01-17 | isbn = 978-0-26202-971-1 | pages = 51–54 | url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=GUFWCgAAQBAJ&redir_esc=y | archive-date = 2021-01-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210128063025/https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=GUFWCgAAQBAJ&redir_esc=y | dead-url = no }}</ref>鲁宾觉得菲尔摆脱循环后不会走回以前的老路，但可能会对再也没有哪天能像最后一个2月2日般完美感到失望，就像他失去超能力一般<ref name="Gilbey-2004" />{{rp|81}}。

== 影响 ==
[[File:Prlaque_of_Movie(Groundhog_day)_Woodstock,_IL.jpg|thumb]]

影评人把《土拨鼠之日》评为影史经典、流行文化试金石，而且是观众认可度在史上名列前茅的喜剧杰作<ref name="Varietyat25" /><ref name="io9classic">{{cite web | first = Charlie Jane | last = Anders | url = https://io9.gizmodo.com/lets-do-the-time-loop-again-and-again-5206173 | title = Let's Do The Time Loop Again. And Again ... | date = 2009-04-10 | website = io9 | access-date = May 2, 2020 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201029202807/https://io9.gizmodo.com/lets-do-the-time-loop-again-and-again-5206173 | archive-date = 2020-10-29 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="EONlineTerm">{{cite web | first = Natalie | last = Finn | title = It's Just Like Groundhog Day—Or Is It? Thanks to the Bill Murray Classic, People Have Never Stopped Saying That | archive-date = 2020-10-29 | dead-url = no | website = [[E!|E!]] | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201029224922/https://www.eonline.com/uk/news/736147/it-s-just-like-groundhog-day-or-is-it-thanks-to-the-bill-murray-classic-people-have-never-stopped-saying-that | date = 2016-02-02 | url = https://www.eonline.com/uk/news/736147/it-s-just-like-groundhog-day-or-is-it-thanks-to-the-bill-murray-classic-people-have-never-stopped-saying-that }}</ref>。2020年，《[[板岩_(杂志)|板岩]]》（''{{lang|en|Paste}}''）杂志声称“只有少数电影”像本片般拥有“历久弥新、宛如神话般的流行文化地位”<ref name="PasteHit" />。影片叫好又叫座，进一步确立雷米斯的喜剧导演地位，为他赢得更多创作机遇<ref>{{cite journal | first = John Evan | last = Frook | title = Columbia Breakdown | url = https://variety.com/1994/film/news/columbia-breakdown-117200/ | date = 1994-01-05 | journal = Variety | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201029191952/https://variety.com/1994/film/news/columbia-breakdown-117200/ | archive-date = 2020-10-29 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="GuardianRamis">{{cite news | first = Andrew | last = Pulver | title = Harold Ramis, Ghostbusters to Groundhog Day – a career in clips | url = https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2014/feb/24/harold-ramis-ghostbusters-groundhog-day-caddyshack-clips | date = 2014-02-24 | newspaper = [[衛報|The Guardian]] | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201029202523/https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2014/feb/24/harold-ramis-ghostbusters-groundhog-day-caddyshack-clips | archive-date = 2020-10-29 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。接下来他继续导演喜剧片，如1996年同样由麦克道威尔主演的《[[丈夫一箩筐|丈夫一箩筐]]》（''{{lang|en|Multiplicity}}''），1999年的《[[教父咪搞|老大靠边闪]]》和2000年的《[[魔女搵老襯|神鬼愿望]]》<ref name="new yorker" /><ref name="GuardianRamis" />。《土拨鼠之日》是证明默瑞演技的作品，让他不再只是喜剧演员，戏路大幅扩张，主演爱情片同样真实可信。本片是他演艺生涯的转折点，此后开始出演众多严肃题材电影，如1998年的《[[青春年少_(电影)|青春年少]]》、获[[奥斯卡最佳男主角奖|奥斯卡最佳男主角奖]]提名的《迷失东京》，以及2012年的《[[月升王国|月升王国]]》。<ref name="TheGuardianDirectors" />鲁宾2007年开办博客，发文虚构他和菲尔·康纳斯的对话，声称菲尔退休后住在[[新墨西哥州|新墨西哥州]][[陶斯_(新墨西哥州)|陶斯]]附近山腰。鲁宾还在[[哈佛大学|哈佛大学]]教授多年编剧。<ref name="VultureRubin" />

电影对伍德斯托克和庞克瑟托尼影响巨大且经久不衰。伍德斯托克在影片上映后开始举办土拨鼠日节庆活动，其中包括名叫伍德斯托克·威利（{{lang|en|Woodstock Willie}}）的土拨鼠<ref name="PennLive" />、电影放映和取景地点徒步旅行<ref name="LocationHub" />。节庆活动约吸引一千游客前来，阿尔伯特、鲁宾和托布罗斯基都曾亮相<ref name="Varietyat25" />。庞克瑟托尼此前的庆祝活动仅有数百人关注，电影发行后数以万计。影片上映次年，3.5万余人到该镇观看土拨鼠日活动<ref name="telegraph interview" /><ref name="Varietyat25" />。当地居民感谢电影对小镇的影响，同时坚信游客关注焦点依然是土拨鼠菲尔和长久坚持举办的节庆活动<ref name="Varietyat25" />。伍德斯托克的重要取景地后来装上牌匾，纪念菲尔遇见内德、菲尔踩入大水坑，以及菲尔与丽塔在城镇广场小亭共舞的情节<ref name="PennLive" /><ref>{{cite news | first = Cassie | last = Buchman | title = Bill Murray returns to Woodstock Square to film Jeep commercial | url = https://www.shawlocal.com/2020/01/25/bill-murray-returns-to-woodstock-square-to-film-jeep-commercial/a3dfuo/ | newspaper = Northwest Herald | date = 2020-01-26 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201029150315/https://www.nwherald.com/2020/01/25/bill-murray-returns-to-woodstock-square-to-film-jeep-commercial/a3dfuo/ | archive-date = 2020-10-29 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

影迷、哲学家和宗教领袖直到2016年还在给鲁宾写信，其中既有普遍信件，又有布道讲演词和论文。精神科医生向病人推荐本片，甚至还有瘾君子来信坦承电影让他们更加充分地意识到自身困境，就像男主角一样身陷循环。<ref name="telegraph interview" /><ref name="VultureRubin" />默瑞在电影上映多年后改变立场，声称《土拨鼠之日》“可能是我最好的作品”，“也可能是哈罗德最优异的作品”<ref name="TheGuardianDirectors" /><ref name="Gilbey-2004" />{{rp|86}}。2018年，托布罗斯基声称默瑞在本片中的“喜剧演出能在电影史上名列前茅……他可以在同一部电影中既演好人又当反派，呈现美好和可怕都能游刃有余……在我看来只要世上还有人拍电影，他就能脱颖而出”<ref name="Varietyat25" />。

=== 时间的考验 ===
众多评论将本片评为影史杰作<ref name="NationalReview" /><ref name="RogerEbertGreat">{{cite web | last = Ebert | first = Roger | title = The shadow of his smile | website = RogerEbert.com | date = 2005-01-30 | url = https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/great-movie-groundhog-day-1993 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201128052819/https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/great-movie-groundhog-day-1993 | archive-date = 2020-11-28 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="Empire500">{{cite journal | first = Willow | last = Green | title = The 500 Greatest Movies Of All Time | date = 2008-10-03 | journal = [[帝國雜誌|Empire]] | url = https://www.empireonline.com/movies/features/500-greatest-movies/ | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108133711/https://www.empireonline.com/movies/features/500-greatest-movies/ | archive-date = 2020-11-08 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="THRJun14">{{cite journal | title = Hollywood's 100 Favorite Films | date = 2014-06-25 | journal = The Hollywood Reporter | access-date = 2021-01-20 | url = https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/100-best-films-ever-hollywood-favorites-818512/item/amelie-hollywoods-100-favorite-films-818437 | archive-date = 2020-11-01 | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201101031311/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/100-best-films-ever-hollywood-favorites-818512/item/amelie-hollywoods-100-favorite-films-818437 }}</ref>。电影参考丛书《[[死前必看的1001部电影|死前必看的1001部电影]]》（''{{lang|en|1001 Movies You Must See Before You Die}}''）写道：<blockquote>……天才般的喜剧片——或许也是20世纪90年代最优异的喜剧片……比尔·默瑞很可能交出演艺生涯最美好、最温暖的答卷……剧情别出心裁，而且又因完全没有解释更上一层楼……还有高明的桥段，如每天早上都在广播电台同样的笑话段子和雪儿夫妇歌曲（《宝贝我了解你》）中醒来；斯蒂芬·托布罗斯基扮演的保险业务员内德·瑞尔森烦人至极，令人拍案叫绝；预先知道事情会如何进展等。《土拨鼠之日》融高明巧妙和捧腹笑料于一体——喜剧难得如此完美。<ref>{{cite book | last = Schneider | first = Steven Jay | title = 1001 Movies You Must See Before You Die | url = https://archive.org/details/1001moviesyoumus0000unse_p9h4 | year = 2013 | publisher = Murdoch Books Pty Limited | location = [[波士顿|Boston]], [[麻薩諸塞州|Massachusetts]] | isbn = 978-0-7641-6613-6}}</ref></blockquote>

2004年，《[[紐約客|紐約客]]》宣布《土拨鼠之日》是雷米斯的代表作<ref name="new yorker" />。伊伯特起初为本片评级三星，但在2005年的《伟大电影》''{{lang|en|The Great Movies}}''系列著作中升至最高的四星<ref name="bigthink rubin" /><ref>{{cite web | first = Robert | last = Tracinski | title = 'Groundhog Day' Has Lasted 25 Years Thanks To Its Unexpected Profundity | date = 2018-01-31 | website = The Federalist | access-date = 2021-01-20 | url = https://thefederalist.com/2018/01/31/groundhog-day-lasted-25-years-thanks-unexpected-profundity/ | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201224233922/https://thefederalist.com/2018/01/31/groundhog-day-lasted-25-years-thanks-unexpected-profundity/ | archive-date = 2020-12-24 | dead-url = no }}</ref>，自承过去低估影片，强调默瑞的演出对本片至关重要<ref name="VultureRubin" /><ref name="RogerEbertGreat" />。专栏作家[[乔纳·戈德堡|乔纳·戈德堡]]（{{lang|en|Jonah Goldberg}}）同年宣布《土拨鼠之日》是过去40年间少有的杰作，称赞影片如同《生活多美好》，非常振奋人心且历久弥新，程度史上少有<ref name="NationalReview" />。2009年，本片入选文学理论家[[斯坦利·费什|斯坦利·费什]]（{{lang|en|Stanley Fish}}）评选的美国十大佳片。在他看来，喜剧与“我们应该如何生活”这种哲学问题本来风马牛不相及，但在本片中却和谐共处、相辅相成，简直令人不敢相信。<ref>{{cite web | first = Stanley | last = Fish | title = The 10 Best American Movies | archive-date = 2020-11-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201109092613/https://opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com//2009/01/04/the-10-best-american-movies/ | url = https://opinionator.blogs.nytimes.com//2009/01/04/the-10-best-american-movies | newspaper = The New York Times | access-date = 2021-01-20 | dead-url = no | date = 2009-01-04 }}</ref>。2020年， “[[Collider|Collider]]”网站也将本片评为影史杰作<ref name="Collider1993" />。《[[衛報|衛報]]》认为影片经久不衰，主要魅力源自类似[[艾比尼澤·史古基|艾比尼澤·史古基]]1843年小说《[[小氣財神|小氣財神]]》重新做人的经典情节，电影没有解释时间循环的原因，进而摆脱主流电影俗套<ref name="TheGuardianDirectors" />。

2000年，[[美国电影学会|美国电影学会]]评选[[AFI百年百大喜劇電影|百年百大喜剧片]]，《土拨鼠之日》排第34<ref>{{cite web | title = AFI's 100 Years...100 Laughs | accessdate = 2021-01-20 | archivedate = 2020-10-09 | url = https://www.afi.com/afis-100-years-100-laughs/ | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201009124238/https://www.afi.com/afis-100-years-100-laughs/ | publisher = [[美国电影学会|American Film Institute]] }}</ref>。2005年，[[美国编剧工会|美国编剧工会]]评选过去75年间101部最佳电影剧本，本片名列第27<ref>{{cite web | title = 101 Greatest Screenplays | url = https://www.wga.org/writers-room/101-best-lists/101-greatest-screenplays | publisher = Writers Guild of America West | year = 2005 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210120002030/https://www.wga.org/writers-room/101-best-lists/101-greatest-screenplays | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = 101 Greatest Screenplays | url = https://www.wga.org/writers-room/101-best-lists/101-greatest-screenplays/list | publisher = Writers Guild of America West | year = 2005 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-date = 2020-12-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201214230050/https://www.wga.org/writers-room/101-best-lists/101-greatest-screenplays/list | dead-url = no }}</ref>。2008年，美国电影学会向1500名电影从业人员开展民意调查，《土拨鼠之日》在所有奇幻片中排名第八<ref>{{cite web | title = AFI Crowns Top 10 Films in 10 Classic Genres | url = https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/46072-afi-crowns-top-10-films-in-10-classic-genres | website = ComingSoon.net | date = 2008-06-18 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210105214902/https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/46072-afi-crowns-top-10-films-in-10-classic-genres | archive-date = 2021-01-05 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = AFI's 10 Top 10 | url = https://www.afi.com/afis-10-top-10/ | publisher = American Film Institute | year = 2008 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210119041113/https://www.afi.com/afis-10-top-10/ | archive-date = 2021-01-19 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。同年《[[帝國雜誌|帝國雜誌]]》评选史上电影五百强，本片名列第259位<ref name="Empire500" />。2014年，《好莱坞报道》邀请2120名电影业界人士评选史上最佳电影，《土拨鼠之日》排第63<ref name="THRJun14" />。2015年，美国编剧工会评选101部最搞笑的剧本，本片仅次于《[[熱情如火|熱情如火]]》和《[[安妮·霍尔|安妮·霍尔]]》名列第三<ref>{{cite web | title = 101 Funniest Screenplays List | url = https://www.wga.org/writers-room/101-best-lists/101-funniest-screenplays/list | publisher = Writers Guild of America West | date = 2015-11-11 | accessdate = 2021-01-20 | archivedate = 2020-11-05 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201105120157/https://www.wga.org/writers-room/101-best-lists/101-funniest-screenplays/list }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Writers Choose 101 Funniest Screenplays | url = https://www.wga.org/news-events/news/press/2015/writers-choose-101-funniest-screenplays | publisher = Writers Guild of America West | date = 2015-11-11 | accessdate = 2021-01-20 | archivedate = 2020-11-02 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201102004828/https://www.wga.org/news-events/news/press/2015/writers-choose-101-funniest-screenplays }}</ref>。2017年，[[英国广播公司|英国广播公司]]向来自52个国家和地区的253位评论家（118男135女）征求意见，评选史上最风趣的一百部电影，《土拨鼠之日》仅次于《安妮·霍尔》、《[[奇爱博士|奇爱博士]]》与《热情如火》名列第四<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20170821-the-100-greatest-comedies-of-all-time | title = The 100 Greatest Comedies of all Time | date = 2017-08-22 | publisher = [[英国广播公司|BBC]] | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201028094859/https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20170821-the-100-greatest-comedies-of-all-time | archivedate = 2020-10-28 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。

