=== 文化影响 ===
[[File:Andiegroundhog.png|thumb]]

[[威廉·戈德曼|威廉·戈德曼]]1993年表示，《土拨鼠之日》属于十年后人们还会记得的那类电影<ref name="bigthink rubin" />。同年德森·汤姆森宣称，[[國會圖書館_(美國)|美国国会图书馆]]永远都不会把本片选入[[國家影片登記表|國家影片登記表]]<ref name="WashingtonPostRevHowe" />。2006年，本片因“文化、历史和美学领域的显著成就”，入选国会图书馆国家影片登记表<ref>{{Cite web | title = Librarian of Congress Adds Home Movie, Silent Films and Hollywood Classics to Film Preservation List | date = 2006-12-27 | issn = 0731-3527 | url = https://www.loc.gov/item/prn-06-234/ | website = [[國會圖書館_(美國)|loc.gov]] | access-date = 2020-10-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201029163936/https://www.loc.gov/item/prn-06-234/ | archive-date = 2020-10-29 | dead-url = yes }}</ref>。

电影人对本片交口称赞，有些还称影片对他们的事业颇具启发，如[[大卫·欧·拉塞尔|大卫·欧·拉塞尔]]、[[特里·瓊斯|特里·瓊斯]]<ref name="TheGuardianDirectors" />和[[杰伊·罗奇|杰伊·罗奇]]（{{lang|en|Jay Roach}}），其中罗奇自称人生因本片改变<ref name="new yorker" />。[[吉莲·威林|吉莲·威林]]（{{lang|en|Gillian Wearing}}）赞扬电影结构别出心裁，哲学意味闪烁智慧光芒，是她非常喜欢的作品<ref name="TheGuardianDirectors" />。影片大获成功，令奇幻题材加速融入主流喜剧片，为将来的奇幻喜剧《[[王牌大騙子|大话王]]》、《[[楚門的世界|楚門的世界]]》，以及《[[命運好好玩_(電影)|人生遥控器]]》打下基础<ref name="TheGuardianDirectors" />。

“土拨鼠之日”成为英语典故，意指一再发生且令人厌烦的单调情境<ref name="TheGuardianDirectors" /><ref>{{cite news | first = Rhonda | title = Strategies: Does your life feel like 'Groundhog Day'? | url = https://www.usatoday.com/story/money/business/small%20business/2015/01/30/small-business-columnist-strategies-groundhog/22380559/ | last = Abrams | newspaper = [[今日美國|USA Today]] | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201025004146/https://www.usatoday.com/story/money/business/small%20business/2015/01/30/small-business-columnist-strategies-groundhog/22380559/ | archive-date = 2020-10-25 | dead-url = no | date = 2015-01-30 }}</ref>。字典提供两种含义，一指节日，二是“不断重复或看似不断重复的情况”<ref>{{cite web | title = Groundhog Day | work = [[柯林斯英语词典|Collins English Dictionary]] | url = https://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/groundhog-day | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170209111426/https://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/groundhog-day | archive-date = 2017-02-09 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | first = Michael | last = Miller | title = City Lights: The spiritual side of 'Groundhog Day' | url = https://www.latimes.com/socal/daily-pilot/entertainment/tn-dpt-xpm-2013-01-31-tn-dpt-0201-city-lights-groundhog-day-20130131-story.html | newspaper = Los Angeles Times | date = 2013-01-31 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201031011528/https://www.latimes.com/socal/daily-pilot/entertainment/tn-dpt-xpm-2013-01-31-tn-dpt-0201-city-lights-groundhog-day-20130131-story.html | archive-date = 2020-10-31 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="SlateTerm">{{cite journal | first1 = Jim | last1 = Pagels | first2 = David | last2 = Haglund | title = For Journalists Who Love Clichés, Every Day is Groundhog Day | url = https://slate.com/culture/2012/02/like-groundhog-day-the-misuse-of-a-new-cliche.html | website = Slate | date = 2012-02-02 | access-date = 2020-11-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201124184856/https://slate.com/culture/2012/02/like-groundhog-day-the-misuse-of-a-new-cliche.html | archive-date = 2020-11-24 | dead-url = no | journal =  }}</ref>，实际应用通常指翻来覆去不断反复的老生常谈<ref name="SlateTerm" />。歌手、体坛名将、笑匠、演员、政治家<ref name="EONlineTerm" /><ref>{{cite news | first = Nick | last = Assinder | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/politics/3458431.stm | title = Prime Ministers Questions | date = 2004-02-04 | publisher = BBC News | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200814143105/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/politics/3458431.stm | archive-date = 2020-08-14 | dead-url = no }}</ref>、大主教<ref name="Gilbey-2004" />{{rp|86}}，乃至前[[关塔那摩湾拘押中心|关塔那摩湾拘押中心]]囚犯都曾使用该词，其中有些还很不恰当<ref>{{cite book | last = Slahi | first = Mohamedou Ould | title = Guantánamo Diary | url = https://archive.org/details/guantnamodiary0000slah | publisher = Little, Brown and Company | location = [[纽约|New York City]], [[纽约州|New York]] | year = 2015 | isbn = 978-0-316-32860-9 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/guantnamodiary0000slah/page/237 237], 311}}</ref>。1996年，美国总统[[比尔·克林顿|比尔·克林顿]]向驻[[波斯尼亚和黑塞哥维那|波斯尼亚]]美军演说时引用该词<ref>{{cite news | first = Dean E. | last = Murphy | title = GI Blues Dull the Response to President | url = https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1996-01-14-mn-24621-story.html | newspaper = Los Angeles Times | date = 1996-01-14 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201030220056/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1996-01-14-mn-24621-story.html | archive-date = 2020-10-30 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。2020年[[2019冠状病毒病疫情|冠状病毒病疫情]]期间，媒体用“土拨鼠之日”意指为阻止病毒传播采取的检疫与隔离措施<ref name="JEEPCovid">{{cite journal | first = David | last = Vinjamuri | title = It's Groundhog Day For Everyone | url = https://www.forbes.com/sites/davidvinjamuri/2020/04/14/its-groundhog-day-for-everyone/#3d7e9d1d19ff | date = 2020-04-14 | journal = Forbes | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201106201848/https://www.forbes.com/sites/davidvinjamuri/2020/04/14/its-groundhog-day-for-everyone/#3d7e9d1d19ff | archive-date = 2020-11-06 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | first = Megan | last = Garber | title = Groundhog Day Was a Horror Movie All Along | url = https://www.theatlantic.com/culture/archive/2020/04/groundhog-day-horror-movie-quarantine/610867/ | journal = [[大西洋_(雜誌)|The Atlantic]] | date = 2020-04-30 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201217073220/https://www.theatlantic.com/culture/archive/2020/04/groundhog-day-horror-movie-quarantine/610867/ | archive-date = 2020-12-17 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

片中人物困在某个时间段的叙事构想可以追溯到1904年，在流行文化、特别是科幻小说中较为多见<ref name="VultureRubin" /><ref name="io9classic" />，但本片上映后才为公众普遍了解。此后许多电影采用时间循环，如《[[婚前性行为_(2000年电影)|婚前性行为]]》（''{{lang|en|Naken}}''，2000年）、《[[啟動原始碼|源代码]]》（2011年）、《[[明日边缘|明日边缘]]》、《[[忌日快樂|忌日快樂]]》和[[祝你忌日快樂|续集]]、《[[棕榈泉_(2020年电影)|棕榈泉]]》（''{{lang|en|Palm Springs}}''，2020年）<ref name="TheGuardianLoop">{{cite news | first = Zach | last = Vasquez | title = Over and over: why is Hollywood still obsessed with Groundhog Day? | url = https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/feb/13/over-and-over-why-is-hollywood-still-obsessed-with-groundhog-day | date = 2019-02-13 | newspaper = The Guardian | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108000109/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/feb/13/over-and-over-why-is-hollywood-still-obsessed-with-groundhog-day | archive-date = 2020-11-08 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = How the 'Palm Springs' Team Found a New Wrinkle in the Time-Loop Movie | archive-date = 2020-11-16 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.theringer.com/movies/2020/7/9/21317708/palm-springs-movie-making-of-andy-samberg-groundhog-day | first = Jake | last = Kring-Schreifels | date = 2020-07-09 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | work = The Ringer | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201116220651/https://www.theringer.com/movies/2020/7/9/21317708/palm-springs-movie-making-of-andy-samberg-groundhog-day }}</ref>，以及电视剧《[[俄羅斯娃娃：派對迴旋|轮回派对]]》<ref name="TheGuardianLoop" />、《[[吸血鬼猎人巴菲|吸血鬼猎人巴菲]]》、《[[夜行天使|暗黑天使]]》和《[[X档案|X档案]]》<ref name="ViceLoop">{{cite journal | first = Pilot | last = Viruet | title = The Pop Culture Legacy of 'Groundhog Day' | url = https://www.vice.com/en/article/ezaapa/the-pop-culture-legacy-of-groundhog-day | date = 2017-02-02 | journal = [[Vice_(雜誌)|Vice]] | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112042401/https://www.vice.com/en/article/ezaapa/the-pop-culture-legacy-of-groundhog-day | archive-date = 2020-11-12 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。这些作品的核心人物大多存在缺陷，必须自我进化才能摆脱时间困局<ref name="TheGuardianLoop" />。《土拨鼠之日》的影响极其显著，“[[TV_Tropes|TV Tropes]]”网站将上述叙事手法称为“土拨鼠之日循环”<ref name="ViceLoop" />。据鲁宾回忆，电影剧本的创作过程颇显“文章本天成，妙手偶得之”，故事本身简单而真实，能从各种不同角度和方式讲述<ref name="telegraph interview" />。本片叙事手法的影响范围不限于影视，1998年的小说《[[关于男孩_(小说)|关于男孩]]》（''{{lang|en|About a Boy}}''）<ref name="Gilbey-2004" />{{rp|7}}、[[克雷格·大衛|克雷格·大衛]]歌曲《[[七天_(歌曲)|七天]]》（{{lang|en|7 Days}}）的音乐视频都有时间循环，《[[異世奇人|異世奇人]]》广播剧《调头》（''{{lang|en|Flip-Flop}}''）中的普克苏托尼行星也是如此<ref name="Gilbey-2004" />{{rp|85}}。

2016年2月2日，英格兰[[利物浦|利物浦]]影迷聚在一起反复观看本片达24小时<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-merseyside-35473935 | date = 2016-02-02 | publisher = BBC News | access-date = 2021-01-20 | title = Groundhog Day for 'hardcore' film fans in Liverpool | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201201022824/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-merseyside-35473935 | archive-date = 2020-12-01 }}</ref>，此后每年2月2日，[[天空电影院|天空电影院]]（{{lang|en|Sky Cinema}}）都会24小时循环播放本片，仅2017年例外<ref>{{cite news | last = Stolworthy | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/groundhog-day-bill-murray-sky-comedy-movies-24-hour-movie-marathon-a9313271.html | title = Groundhog Day: Sky showing a 24-hour marathon of movie to celebrate | newspaper = [[獨立報|The Independent]] | first = Jacob | date = 2020-02-02 | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201121100441/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/groundhog-day-bill-murray-sky-comedy-movies-24-hour-movie-marathon-a9313271.html | archive-date = 2020-11-21 | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last1 = Babbage | first1 = Rachel | last2 = Davies | first2 = Megan | url = https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a782041/sky-cinema-comedy-groundhog-day-repeated-showings/ | title = Sky Cinema Comedy is celebrating Groundhog Day with continuous showings of Groundhog Day... again | date = 2019-02-02 | website = [[數碼間諜|Digital Spy]] | access-date = 2021-01-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201030204705/https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a782041/sky-cinema-comedy-groundhog-day-repeated-showings/ | archive-date = 2020-10-30 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。2018年，纽约[[現代藝術博物館|現代藝術博物館]]首度放映35名文学和宗教学者投票选出的电影，其中第一部就是《土拨鼠之日》，许多学者都想为影片撰写介绍文稿，以致为此发生冲突<ref name="NationalReview" />。

